        <para id="id65212">If two polygons are <emphasis effect="italics">similar</emphasis>, one is an enlargement of the other. This means that the two polygons will have the same angles and their sides will be in the same proportion.</para>
        <para id="id65223">We use the symbol <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mo>|||</m:mo></m:math> to mean <emphasis effect="italics">is similar to</emphasis>.</para>
<definition id="fhsst_id537"><term id="termfhsst_id537"> Similar Polygons </term> <meaning id="meaningfhsst_id537">
        <para id="id65247">Two polygons are similar if:</para>
        <list id="id65253" display="block" list-type="enumerated">
          <item id="uid30">their corresponding angles are equal, <emphasis effect="bold">and</emphasis></item>
          <item id="uid31">the ratios of corresponding sides are equal.
</item>
        </list>
        
        </meaning></definition>
<exercise id="secfhsst_id546"><title> Similarity of Polygons </title>
        <problem id="probfhsst_id547">
        <para id="id65309">Show that the following two polygons are similar.</para>
        <para id="id65315">
          <figure id="id65318">
            <media id="id65318_media" alt="">
              <image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/MG10C14_011.png" id="id65318_onlineimage" width="307"><!-- NOTE: attribute width changes image size online (pixels). original width is 307. --></image>
              <image mime-type="application/postscript" for="pdf" src="../../media/MG10C14_011.eps" id="id65318_printimage"/>
            </media>
          </figure>
        </para>
        
        </problem>
        <solution id="solfhsst_id559"> <list id="listfhsst_id559" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic" class="stepwise">
        <item> <label> Determine what is required </label>
        <para id="id65346">We are required to show that the pair of polygons is similar. We can do this by showing that the ratio of corresponding sides is equal and by showing that corresponding angles are equal.</para>
        </item> <item> <label> Corresponding angles </label>
        <para id="id65355">We are given the angles. So, we can show that corresponding angles are equal.</para>
        </item> <item> <label> Show that corresponding angles are equal </label>
        <para id="id65363">All angles are given to be 90<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msup><m:mrow/><m:mo>∘</m:mo></m:msup></m:math> and</para>
        <equation id="id65380">
          <m:math overflow="scroll" mode="display">
            <m:mtable displaystyle="true">
